data.prompt: a website about retro computers
data.html:
Retro Computers

Welcome to our website dedicated to the nostalgia of old computers!

Commodore 64

The Commodore 64 was a popular home computer of the 1980s. It had a MOS Technology 6510 microprocessor running at 1 MHz and came with 64 kilobytes of RAM. Many people still use this computer today, and there are even new games and software being developed for it!

Apple II

The Apple II was released in 1977 and was one of the first successful personal computers. It had an MOS Technology 6502 processor running at 1 MHz and came with 4 kilobytes of RAM. Many people used the Apple II for games or programming, and it was often used in schools as well.
